This is the EIONET datadictionary software.

Read the doc/installationmanual.doc for installation instructions


Quick Start - Installation Guide

The following short installation guide gives some quick hints how to checkout DD code from SVN and set it up as a Tomcat web application

1. Create build directory for SVN checkout
shell>cd /var/local/build
shell>svn checkout https://svn.eionet.europa.eu/repositories/Reportnet/datadict/trunk datadict

2. Create DD database and database user in MySql
mysql>create database DataDict;
mysql>CREATE USER 'dduser'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'password';
mysql>GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON DataDict.* TO 'dduser'@'localhost'

3. Import initial database structure and init data
shell>cd datadict/sql
shell>mysql -u root -p DataDict < dd-struct.sql
shell>mysql -u root -p DataDict < dd-attrs-meta.sql
shell>mysql -u root -p DataDict < help-data.sql

4. create build.properties file by duplicating default.properties
shell>cp default.properties build.properties

5. modify the following environment specific properties in build.properties:
app.name=Data Dictionary
app.home=/var/local/seionet-java/datadict_contents
webapp.home=/var/local/datadict_apps/ROOT
servletapi.jar=/var/lib/tomcat/common/lib/servlet-api.jar
#Note! Correct version of MySQl jdbc type 4 driver should be downloaded and copied into Tomcat lib folder
lib-mysql-connector-jar==/var/lib/tomcat/common/lib/mysql-connector-java-5.1.15-bin.jar
db.* - database specific properties
dd.url=http://dd.eionet.europa.eu
dd.host=dd.eionet.europa.eu

6. Revise UNS properties in src/datadict.properties.tmpl (optional)

7. Revise /custom/*.txt files for modifying header texts and links (optional)

8. Setup Tomcat context in server.xml:
copy the <Context> element from datadict/context.xml into tomcat/conf/server.xml betrween <Host> element.

9. Run ant install in datadict root folder and restart Tomcat
shell>ant install


Additional web applications are available for modfying user privileges and help texts in DD:
AclAdmin tool: https://svn.eionet.europa.eu/repositories/Reportnet/acladmin/trunk
HelpAdmin tool: https://svn.eionet.europa.eu/repositories/Reportnet/helpadmin/trunk

Installing these applciations follows the similar steps:
1. Checkout from SVN
2. Create build.properties from default.properties
3. Modify environment specific properties in build.properties file
4. call "ant install"
5. Rename acladmin.properties.dist/helpadmin.properties.dist to acladmin.properties/helpadmin.properties in ROOT/WEB-INF/classes folder and revise the content of the properties files
6. Rename *.acl.dist files to *.acl files in acladmin_contents/acls folder (only in AclAdminTool) and revise the contents of acladmin.gorpu file
7. Create contexts for both applications in tomcat/conf/server.xml and restart Tomcat



